Ah, I think I follow. You loop to the left, if no more left then you loop to the right.

I think this may be clearer as two separate loops, i.e. like this:

/* look for available subnets before startSub */
currentSub = autoalloc.decrementSubnet(startSub, plen);
while (currentSub && self.us_npushed < 16) {
    self.pushToStream(currentSub);
    currentSub = autoalloc.decrementSubnet(currentSub, plen);
}

if (self.us_npushed >= 16) {
    done();
    return;
}

/* look for available subnets after endSub */
currentSub = autoalloc.incrementSubnet(endSub, plen);
while (currentSub && self.us_npushed < 16) {
    self.pushToStream(currentSub);
    currentSub = autoalloc.incrementSubnet(currentSub, plen);
}

done();

